19.Que==Which tool can help you to compare the cost of hosting resources in AWS vs the cost of hosting in a traditional data centre?
ans-Aws TCO Calculator
exp-The TCO calculators allow you to estimate the cost savings when using AWS and provide a detailed set of reports. Pricing Calculator can be used to estimate potential AWS spend, and AWS Budgets & Billing Alarms can help keep spend under control by alerting you when you breach a threshold
20.For AWS Enterprise customers, the AWS Concierge is a resource dedicated to answering billing and account questions
21.Reserved instances have three main pricing models, Standard, Convertible and Scheduled
22.EC2 Reserved Instances offer significant discounts for a contracted term-of-service, of up to 75% off. On-Demand instances are charged equally per-hour, regardless of how long they’re run for. Spot instances are cheaper than On-Demand instances, but aren’t intended for long term use
